    "html": "<h1 id=\"cli-commands\">Slice.js CLI Commands</h1>\r\n<p>\r\n  Slice.js comes with a powerful command-line interface (CLI) that helps you create, manage, and run your Slice.js applications. \r\n  The CLI is organized into logical command groups for better workflow management.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"commands-section\">\r\n  <h2 id=\"project-lifecycle\">Project Lifecycle Commands</h2>\r\n  <div class=\"commands-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"init-command\">Initialize Project</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:init</code> command sets up a new Slice.js project with the proper folder structure and configuration files.\r\n          It's the first command you should run when starting a new Slice.js project.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"init-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"dev-command\">Development Server</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:dev</code> or <code>slice:start</code> command starts the development server for your Slice.js application.\r\n          It serves your application from the /src directory and provides live reloading.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"dev-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"commands-section\">\r\n  <h2 id=\"local-components\">Local Component Management</h2>\r\n  <div class=\"commands-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"create-command\">Create Component</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:component create</code> command helps you create new local components with the proper structure.\r\n          It generates the JavaScript, HTML, and CSS files for your component.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"create-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"list-command\">List Components</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:component list</code> command shows you all available components in your local project.\r\n          This is useful for seeing what components you have and where they're located.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"list-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"delete-command\">Delete Component</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:component delete</code> command allows you to safely remove components from your local project.\r\n          It ensures all files related to the component are properly deleted.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"delete-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"commands-section\">\r\n  <h2 id=\"registry-components\">Registry Component Management</h2>\r\n  <div class=\"commands-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"get-command\">Get Components</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:get</code> command downloads and installs components from the official Slice.js repository.\r\n          You can install multiple components at once and specify options like force overwrite or service components.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"get-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"browse-command\">Browse Components</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:browse</code> command shows you all available components in the official repository.\r\n          This helps you discover new components and understand what's available for installation.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"browse-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"sync-command\">Sync Components</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:sync</code> command updates all your local components to the latest versions from the repository.\r\n          This ensures you have the most recent bug fixes and improvements.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"sync-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"commands-section\">\r\n  <h2 id=\"maintenance\">Maintenance Commands</h2>\r\n  <div class=\"commands-grid\">\r\n    <div class=\"command-card\">\r\n      <h3 id=\"version-command\">Version & Updates</h3>\r\n      <div class=\"command-description\">\r\n        <p>\r\n          The <code>slice:version</code> and <code>slice:update</code> commands help you check your current version\r\n          and look for available updates for both the CLI and the Slice.js framework.\r\n        </p>\r\n        <div class=\"version-example\"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"workflow\">Complete CLI Workflow</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n  When developing with Slice.js, you typically follow a comprehensive workflow that involves multiple command categories\r\n  working together. Here's how all the commands work together:\r\n</p>\r\n<div class=\"command-workflow\"></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"best-practices\">\r\n  <h2 id=\"best-practices\">CLI Best Practices</h2>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>Always run <code>slice:init</code> first when creating a new project</li>\r\n    <li>Use <code>slice:dev</code> for development and keep it running during development</li>\r\n    <li>Use <code>slice:component create</code> to ensure components follow the proper structure</li>\r\n    <li>Use <code>slice:get</code> to install official components from the repository</li>\r\n    <li>Run <code>slice:sync</code> regularly to keep components updated</li>\r\n    <li>Use <code>slice:build</code> before deploying to production</li>\r\n    <li>Check for updates with <code>slice:update</code> periodically</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"cli-tips\">\r\n  <h3>Pro Tips</h3>\r\n  <p>\r\n    <strong>Command Groups:</strong> The CLI is organized into logical groups for better workflow management:\r\n  </p>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Project Lifecycle:</strong> <code>init</code>, <code>dev</code>, <code>start</code></li>\r\n    <li><strong>Local Components:</strong> <code>component create</code>, <code>component list</code>, <code>component delete</code></li>\r\n    <li><strong>Registry Operations:</strong> <code>get</code>, <code>browse</code>, <code>sync</code></li>\r\n    <li><strong>Production:</strong> <code>build</code></li>\r\n    <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> <code>version</code>, <code>update</code></li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  \r\n  <p>\r\n    <strong>Multiple Terminals:</strong> For the best development experience, keep one terminal running \r\n    <code>slice:dev</code> and use another terminal for other commands.\r\n  </p>\r\n  \r\n  <p>\r\n    <strong>Component Categories:</strong> When creating components, choose the appropriate category:\r\n  </p>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Visual:</strong> For UI components that users interact with (requires HTML, CSS, JS)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Service:</strong> For components that provide functionality but no UI (JS only)</li>\r\n    <li><strong>AppComponents:</strong> For application-specific components (JS only)</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  \r\n  <p>\r\n    <strong>Registry vs Local:</strong> Use <code>slice:get</code> for official components and \r\n    <code>slice:component create</code> for custom components specific to your project.\r\n  </p>\r\n</div>",
